Class WordTestDateUtility

java.lang.Object
  org.catechis.WordTestDateUtility

public class WordTestDateUtility
extends java.lang.Object

This utility class takes a Word object and recordes the last type-specific test and what level the word is at after/before??? the test.

evaluateWordsFirstTestDate

public java.lang.String evaluateWordsFirstTestDate(Word word)
This method finds the first date a word was tested.

reading or writing tests are both considered.

Test files were named like this:

level 0 reading.test

Daily tests created a name like this for backwards compatibilty.

Really old tests were vague about the level they were testing, but those dates are still important. THey look like this:

basic_writing.test

or

basic_ten_word.test

In these cases, we just add the date of the test.

getWordsFirstTestTime

public long getWordsFirstTestTime()

getWordTestTimes

public java.util.Vector getWordTestTimes()
THis method collects the test dates in a long number format, subtracts each one from the words_first_test_time, and returns a Vector of the times so that a Y axis plot of the tests will be a number of millisecornds from the first date of entry or the first test date.
